ck&lt;BR&gt;&gt; - Keep Ca=\r\nmphor, Rice mixed with ghee and turmeric, Flowers, etc... ready. (I do not\n=\r\n use flowers any more. Use Akshatas mixed with Turmeric as flowers..Bhagwan=\r\n ko bolta hun BhavnaO ko Samjho! Phul ki jagape Chawal se kaam chalalo:-)&lt;B=\r\nR&gt;&gt; &lt;BR&gt;&gt; So when I get ready for Homam, I just have to fill up the c=\r\nopper tumbler with water and heat up the ghee and few other such activities=\r\n which takes around 5to7 Minutes in total.&lt;BR&gt;&gt; &lt;BR&gt;&gt; Before i forget=\r\n i must remind that there is no need to keep the Darbha in 4 directions eve=\r\nry time. One can keep those Darbhas at the same place as many days as possi=\r\nble.&lt;BR&gt;&gt; &lt;BR&gt;&gt; &lt;BR&gt;&gt; Please ignore this Fool if the post did not =\r\nmake much sense.&lt;BR&gt;&gt; Yours,&lt;BR&gt;&gt; &lt;BR&gt;&gt; HavanOtpal&lt;BR&gt;&gt; &lt;BR&gt;&gt=\r\n; &lt;BR&gt;&gt; --- In &lt;A href=3D&quot;mailto:vedic-wisdom%40yahoogroups.com&quot; rel=3Dn=\r\nofollow target=3D_blank ymailto=3D&quot;mailto:vedic-wisdom%40yahoogroups.com&quot;&gt;v=\r\nedic-wisdom@yahoogroups.com&lt;/A&gt;, Nagraj Kota &lt;nagraj_um@&gt; wrote:&lt;BR&gt;&=\r\ngt; &gt;&lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; That was=C3=82&nbsp;a nice post Ajit. I am also one o=\r\nf\n those people who, because of guilt factor of skipping sandhyavandana, un=\r\nable to do the homa daily. I do it every week. But there is a little other =\r\nlogistics issue for me. I live in the US and I do my homa in my living room=\r\n where the Wood burning Fireplace (east facing)=C3=82&nbsp;is located. My p=\r\nooja room however, is in a different location towards north of the house. I=\r\n have a big Shiva Lingam in my pooja room for which I do daily abhishekam i=\r\nn the morning, (with Rudra Adhyaya on Mondays). So, if I have do both nithy=\r\napooja and homam daily, it is really time taking as arranging for homam tak=\r\nes almost 20 minutes, on a routine basis. Any ideas for managing this bette=\r\nr? Fo