.&lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; &lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; If you look at au=\r\npAsana procedures, you will find that Narasimha&#39;s&lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; manual is mo=\r\nre elaborate than the aupAsana. Homa is basically a&lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; superset o=\r\nf aupAsana. Where the manual differs, it is more relevant&lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; for =\r\nour modern lifestyle, and you don&#39;t need to add anything to it.&lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt=\r\n; Frankly, I basically follow Narasimha&#39;s manual, but say &quot;aupAsana&quot; in&lt;BR&gt;=\r\n&gt; &gt; the sankalpa. They are that similar. The fire in which you do&lt;BR&gt;=\r\n&gt; &gt; &quot;upAsana&quot; is &quot;aupAsana&quot;.&lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; &lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; bhavadiiyaH,&lt;=\r\nBR&gt;&gt; &gt; &lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; ajit&lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt;&lt;BR&gt;&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/D=\r\nIV&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/body&gt;&lt;/html&gt;\r\n--0-780106026-1309242165=:62811--\r\n\n"}}